Upcoming act, Bello Hameed Tomiwa aka   Hdot has expressed how Grammy-winning Burna Boy inspires him to greatness. The 22-year-old Hdot noted that Burna Boy inspires his optimism to extend his music across the globe to touch lives while currently working on a project under Legend Records.   Shoot Your Shot: Chef Sommy cooks up date to win crush’s…     I married who I wasn’t supposed to marry, says Kas Beats     Why I’m different from other musicians, says Berri-Tiga   The Nigerian singer, songwriter, instrumentalist, and record producer, started music in 2015, after falling in love with Qdot’s songs. He explained Qdot’s singing style made him discover his musical talent and also motivated his moniker, Hdot. After featuring popular acts like Zlatan Ibile and Ayanfe, Hdot has released songs that include ‘Duro,’ ‘Eminent,’ and ‘Time.’